* dotscript_expr_regression.dts
* Proves DotScript memory variables (VAR / $name) and arrays ({} literals, one-based
* $a[n] subscripts, nested/chained) through the house expression path, plus an IF
* literal baseline that the expression-path convergence (AIF-041) must keep green.
*
* Self-asserting: each R# check prints "<TAG>:.T." on success (a value comparison
* evaluated in the expression path) or "<TAG>:.F." on failure. Each B# baseline prints
* ":PASS". A passing run shows every tag ":.T." / ":PASS" and both BEGIN/END markers.
* Note: the comparison is wrapped in parentheses on purpose (so '=' is a comparison,
* not an assignment, and binds before the '+').
*
* Fixture-free: pure expression + literal predicates; no table required.
*
* Run:  REGRESSION RUN DOTSCRIPT_EXPR
*   or: DOTSCRIPT dottalkpp/data/scripts/dotscript/dotscript_expr_regression.dts
*
* Self-bootstrap the environment (regression doctrine: every test sets its own
* environment; the ambient default is STOP_ON_ERROR OFF). R8 deliberately triggers
* an out-of-range error, so this test REQUIRES STOP_ON_ERROR OFF to reach B1/B2 --
* set it explicitly so the test is correct even when run right after ERRORSTOP
* (whose Phase-2 abort leaves the policy ON). ECHO OFF keeps the judged region clean
* regardless of a prior CALC run leaving ECHO ON.
SET ECHO OFF
STOP_ON_ERROR OFF

FORMULA "DOTSCRIPT-EXPR-REGRESSION-BEGIN"

* --- VAR memory variables: store then read back as $name ---
VAR n = 40 + 2
? "R1_var_scalar:" + ($n = 42)

VAR label = UPPER("hi")
? "R2_var_string_fn:" + ($label = "HI")

* --- arrays: {} literal + one-based $a[n] subscript ---
VAR a = {10, 20, 30}
? "R3_array_subscript:" + ($a[2] = 20)
? "R4_array_subscript_arith:" + (($a[2] + 5) = 25)
? "R5_var_case_insensitive:" + ($A[3] = 30)

* --- nested array + chained subscript ---
VAR m = {1, {2, 3}}
? "R6_array_nested_chained:" + ($m[2][1] = 2)

* --- whole-array display (documented expected: {array:3}) ---
? "R7_array_display_expect_{array:3}:"
? $a

* --- out-of-range subscript (documented expected: a FORMULA error line) ---
? "R8_out_of_range_expect_error:"
? $a[9]

* --- IF literal baseline: predicate path must stay correct through the convergence ---
IF (1 = 1)
  FORMULA "B1_if_true_literal:PASS"
ELSE
  FORMULA "B1_if_true_literal:FAIL"
ENDIF

IF (2 > 3)
  FORMULA "B2_if_false_literal:FAIL"
ELSE
  FORMULA "B2_if_false_literal:PASS"
ENDIF

FORMULA "DOTSCRIPT-EXPR-REGRESSION-END"
